description: EarthLabs Inc. operates as a technology services company in mineral exploration in Canada. The company operates in two segments, Exploration Technology Division and Financial Technology Division. The Exploration Technology Division segment offers LithoLens, a proprietary core imaging technology that automatically and consistently examines old core images to create fresh and accurate geological logs; MinusOne, a proprietary geophysical data inversion platform for creating 3-D models from geophysical data processed using deterministic and stochastic inversion methods; GeoFEZ, a processing software that extracts new insight from common exploration data, such as potential field data, topographic data, hyperspectral data, radiometric data, and electromagnetic data; and multi-parameter acquisition survey system, which allows the simultaneous capture of gradient magnetics, LiDAR, 4-band orthophoto imagery, and electromagnetic information in the very low frequency band and radiometric data. This segment also provides GeoticLog, a customizable core-logging platform; GeoticMine, a 3-D geological modelling and visualization solution; GeoticSection, a drill-hole visualizer; GeoticCAD, an industry tool with an integrated drawing motor; and GeoticField, a field-based survey data entry platform. The Financial Technology Division segment offers Resource Quantamental, an artificial intelligence decision engine for investments; CEO.CA, a social network for investors and traders in junior resource and venture stocks with online and mobile functionality; and DigiGeoAtlas platform, a software-based GIS interactive mapping interface alongside its DigiGeoMaps distribution business, as well as provides a range of cloud-based and interoperable web applications. This segment also provides smart targets, image analytics, geophysics, structural geology, geochemistry, and field geology services. The company was formerly known as GoldSpot Discoveries Corp. and changed its name to EarthLabs Inc. in September 2022. EarthLabs Inc. is headquartered in Toronto, Canada.
ceo: Mr. Denis Roland Laviolette B.Sc, B.Sc.
